The 12789 / 12790 Murdeshwar – Kacheguda Superfast Express is an Superfast Express train belonging to South Central Railway zone that runs between  and Kacheguda (Hyderabad) in India. It is currently being operated with 12789/12790 train numbers on bi-weekly basis. Earlier the train used run between  and  The train got extended till  With effect from 11th October 2024.
Service
The 12790/Murdeshwar–Kacheguda SF Express has an average speed of 53 km/h and covers 1688 km in 32h. The 12789/Kacheguda–Murdeshwar SF Express has an average speed of 52 km/h and covers 1688 km in 32h 10m.

Coach composition
The train has standard LHB rakes with a maximum speed of 130 km/h. The train consists of 22 coaches:
* 1 AC First Class
* 2 AC II Tier
* 6 AC III Tier
* 6 Sleeper coaches
* 4 General Unreserved
* 1 End On Generator cum Luggage Rake
* 1 Pantry Car
* 1 SLR
Traction
Both trains are hauled Erode Loco Shed &  Lalaguda Loco shed-based WAP-4 & WAP-7 electric locomotive from Mangalore to Kacheguda.
Rake sharing
The train shares its rake with 22715/22716 Kacheguda–Madurai Weekly Express.
